        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3076422859" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8506792189796305399">A debut novel by two Princeton grads, this story has a Dan Brown quality immersing the reader into the Renaissance years while the main two characters work to uncover the meaning of a mysterious book written in 1499. Well researched, paced and developed it engages the reader, raises questions and demonstrates good storytelling. The only fault I can find is somewhat of a let down with the finale. This isn&apos;t uncommon with first books though it did diminish the six years of work the authors investe</span>
  <span id="freeText8506792189796305399" style="display:none">A debut novel by two Princeton grads, this story has a Dan Brown quality immersing the reader into the Renaissance years while the main two characters work to uncover the meaning of a mysterious book written in 1499. Well researched, paced and developed it engages the reader, raises questions and demonstrates good storytelling. The only fault I can find is somewhat of a let down with the finale. This isn't uncommon with first books though it did diminish the six years of work the authors invested. Regardless, I enjoyed it thoroughly and recommend it to anyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8506792189796305399" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

